properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued January 28 at 9:23AM PST until January 29 at 10:00PM PST by NWS Los Angeles/Oxnard CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...North winds 15 to 25 mph with gusts up to 40 mph.

* WHERE...Santa Barbara County South Coast.

* WHEN...Until 10 PM PST Wednesday.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds will blow around unsecured objects and
make driving difficult, especially for high profile vehicles.
Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may
result.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Highways 101 and 154 will be affected with
the strongest winds in the Montecito Hills, San Marcos Pass, and
Gaviota/Refugio areas.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 PM PST WEDNESDAY
